[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA libFuzzer timeout error has been encountered during fuzzing operations. This [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicates that the fuzzer has detected code execution that exceeds the configured [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimeout threshold, suggesting the presence of computationally expensive operations,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minfinite loops, or algorithmic complexity issues that prevent the fuzzer from [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompleting execution within the expected timeframe.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe issue manifests as a [0m[32m"libFuzzer: timeout"[0m[39m error, which is a critical signal [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfrom the fuzzing infrastructure. This error type specifically indicates that:[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Nature of the Issue:**[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer has identified an input or code path that causes execution time to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexceed the predefined timeout limit[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This is not a crash or assertion failure, but rather a hang or extremely slow [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexecution scenario[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The timeout mechanism is a safety feature to prevent the fuzzer from getting [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstuck indefinitely on problematic inputs[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Vulnerability Implications:**[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWhile not explicitly stated as a specific vulnerability type, timeout issues can [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicate:[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Potential Denial of Service [0m[1;39m([0m[39mDoS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m vulnerabilities where malicious inputs could [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcause resource exhaustion[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Algorithmic complexity vulnerabilities [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., ReDoS for regular expressions, or [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mquadratic/exponential time complexity issues[0m[1;39m)[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Infinite loop conditions that could be triggered by specific input patterns[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Resource exhaustion scenarios including excessive memory allocation or CPU [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconsumption[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Important Observations:**[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The timeout suggests deterministic or near-deterministic behavior that can be [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreproduced with specific inputs[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- LibFuzzer has successfully identified a test case that triggers this behavior, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich should be available for analysis[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The issue may only manifest with certain input characteristics [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize, content, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructure, or edge cases[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This could affect system availability and performance in production environments[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Investigation Areas:**[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo obtain a comprehensive understanding of this issue, the following areas of the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcodebase should be examined:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Input Processing Logic**: Areas where external input is parsed, validated, or [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocessed, particularly loops and recursive functions that depend on input [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcharacteristics[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Algorithmic Implementations**: Functions with potential complexity issues, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincluding:[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Nested loops where iteration counts depend on input[0m                            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - String matching or pattern matching algorithms[0m                                 [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Resource Allocation Patterns**: Code sections that allocate resources based on[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minput parameters, which could lead to excessive allocation attempts[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Termination Conditions**: Loop conditions and recursion base cases that might [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnot be properly validated against edge cases[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39manalyzed to understand the characteristics that lead to the problematic behavior[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Recent Changes**: Any recent modifications to core processing logic, [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparticularly changes that might have introduced unbounded operations[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe investigation should focus on identifying code paths that lack proper bounds [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecking, timeout mechanisms, or complexity limits that would prevent excessive [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexecution time when processing adversarial or edge-case inputs.[0m                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m76[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mToken[0m[1;39m([0m[39mchar character, Kind type[0m[1;39m)[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m77[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m78[0m[39m:        this.text = [0m[1;35mCharacter.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcharacter[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m79[0m[39m:        this.kind = type;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m80[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m81[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m82[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m83[0m[39m:     * Constructs a new Token object given its raw data and kind.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m84[0m[39m:     * This is for CHARSTRING tokens only.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m85[0m[39m:     * @param data[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m86[0m[39m:     * @param type[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m87[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m88[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mToken[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m data, Kind type[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m89[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m90[0m[39m:        this.data = data;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m91[0m[39m:        this.kind = type;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m92[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m93[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m94[0m[39m:    public String [0m[1;35mgetText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m95[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m96[0m[39m:        return text;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m97[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m98[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m99[0m[39m:    public Kind [0m[1;35mgetKind[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m100[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfontbox/src/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/type1/Type1Parser.jav[0m[1;92ma:217[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m223[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m217[0m[39m:            while [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mlexer.peekKind[0m[1;39m([0m[39mToken.NAME[0m[1;39m)[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m218[0m[39m:                    && [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"dup"[0m[1;39m)[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m219[0m[39m:                            || [0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"readonly"[0m[1;39m)[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m220[0m[39m:                            || [0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"def"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m221[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m222[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mlexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m223[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfontbox/src/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/type1/Type1Parser.jav[0m[1;92ma:640[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m644[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m640[0m[39m:        while [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mlexer.peekKind[0m[1;39m([0m[39mToken.LITERAL[0m[1;39m)[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m641[0m[39m:                && [0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"CharStrings"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m642[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m643[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35mlexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m644[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBased on the evaluation report and code snippets, I've identified the root cause of[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe libFuzzer timeout error:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Root Cause[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe timeout is caused by two infinite loop vulnerabilities in `Type1Parser.java`:[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Vulnerability [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m217[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m223[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: In `[0m[1;35mreadEncoding[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Vulnerability [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m640[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m644[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: In `[0m[1;35mparseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBoth vulnerabilities share the same pattern: unbounded while loops that scan for [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexpected tokens but fail to check for EOF [0m[1;39m([0m[39mEnd of File[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. When malformed font data [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlacks the expected tokens, the loops continue indefinitely consuming null tokens at[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mEOF, causing the fuzzer to timeout.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Mechanism of Failure[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWhen EOF is reached:[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` returns `null`[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;35mlexer.peekKind[0m[1;39m([0m[39mToken.NAME/LITERAL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` returns `false` [0m[1;39m([0m[39msafe null check inside[0m[1;39m)[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Loop condition evaluates: `![0m[1;39m([0m[39mfalse && [0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` = `true`[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;35mlexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is called repeatedly, returning `null` each time[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Loop never terminates → timeout[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Code Evidence[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe codebase already has multiple examples of correct EOF handling:[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Lines [0m[1;36m476[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m478[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m515[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m518[0m[39m: `[0m[1;35mreadProc[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mreadProcVoid[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` check for null [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimmediately[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Lines [0m[1;36m557[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m563[0m[39m: `[0m[1;35mparseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` has a correct pattern for finding [0m[32m"/Private"[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Lines [0m[1;36m397[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m399[0m[39m: `[0m[1;35mreadValue[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` checks for null in array parsing[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Lines [0m[1;36m334[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m344[0m[39m: `[0m[1;35mreadSimpleDict[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` has multiple null checks[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Location [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: `[0m[1;35mreadEncoding[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m217[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m223[0m[1;39m)[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Current vulnerable code:**[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhile [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mlexer.peekKind[0m[1;39m([0m[39mToken.NAME[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        && [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"dup"[0m[1;39m)[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                || [0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"readonly"[0m[1;39m)[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                || [0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"def"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mlexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Fix approach:**[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAdd an EOF check inside the loop body. When `[0m[1;35mlexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` returns null, throw[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man `IOException` with a descriptive message indicating that the expected tokens [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[32m"dup"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"readonly"[0m[39m, or [0m[32m"def"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m were not found before EOF.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Implementation steps:**[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Capture the return value of `[0m[1;35mlexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in a variable[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Check if the token is null[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. If null, throw an `IOException` with message: [0m[32m"Unexpected end of file while [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mreading encoding. Expected 'dup', 'readonly', or 'def'"[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Location [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: `[0m[1;35mparseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m640[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m644[0m[1;39m)[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Current vulnerable code:**[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhile [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mlexer.peekKind[0m[1;39m([0m[39mToken.LITERAL[0m[1;39m)[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        && [0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"CharStrings"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mlexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Fix approach:**[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAdd the same EOF check pattern. When `[0m[1;35mlexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` returns null, throw an [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`IOException` indicating that [0m[32m"CharStrings"[0m[39m was not found.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Implementation steps:**[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Capture the return value of `[0m[1;35mlexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in a variable[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Check if the token is null[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. If null, throw an `IOException` with message: [0m[32m"Unexpected end of file while [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mlooking for CharStrings"[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why This is the Optimal Approach[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Consistency with codebase patterns**: The fix aligns with existing EOF [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandling patterns used throughout `Type1Parser.java` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mas seen in `[0m[1;35mreadProc[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mreadProcVoid[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;35mreadValue[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Minimal invasiveness**: The fix only adds [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m4[0m[39m lines per vulnerable loop, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecking for null and throwing an appropriate exception. No changes to the overall [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic or flow.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Preserves existing functionality**: The loops still scan for the same tokens; [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwe only add safety checks to prevent infinite loops on malformed input.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Clear error messages**: The exceptions provide diagnostic information about [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhat was expected and where the failure occurred, aiding debugging.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Fail-fast behavior**: Rather than hanging indefinitely, the parser now fails [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimmediately when EOF is reached without finding expected tokens, which is the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcorrect behavior for malformed fonts.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **No impact on valid fonts**: Valid Type [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m fonts will contain the expected [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtokens, so the EOF check will never trigger for well-formed input.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Potential Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Side effect**: Previously [0m[32m"tolerated"[0m[39m malformed fonts [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthose missing required [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtokens[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m will now throw exceptions instead of hanging.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Mitigation**: This is actually the desired behavior. The Type [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m font format [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mspecification requires these tokens, and the parser's purpose is to parse [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwell-formed fonts. Malformed fonts should be rejected with clear error messages [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrather than causing timeouts or resource exhaustion.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Test compatibility**: The fix should not break existing tests because:[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Valid test fonts contain the required tokens[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Any tests using malformed fonts that were timing out will now fail fast with [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexceptions[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The parser's public API remains unchanged[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Referenced Similar Solutions[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fix follows the exact pattern established in the same file:[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Lines [0m[1;36m476[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m478[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mreadProc[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Checks `if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m == null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthrows IOException[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Lines [0m[1;36m515[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m518[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mreadProcVoid[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Identical pattern[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Lines [0m[1;36m557[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m564[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mparseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - earlier section[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Uses null check in while [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcondition and stores token in variable[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis demonstrates that the codebase authors understand proper EOF handling; the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvulnerable loops are outliers that need to be brought into conformance with the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mestablished patterns.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue reports a libFuzzer timeout error in the codebase. A patch was [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempted that adds null checks for tokens returned by `[0m[1;35mlexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in two [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocations within the `Type1Parser.java` file. The patch aimed to detect unexpected [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mend-of-file conditions and throw `IOException` with descriptive messages. However, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mafter applying the patch, the libFuzzer timeout error persists, indicating the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch did not resolve the underlying issue.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is a libFuzzer timeout error. This type of error typically occurs[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhen the fuzzing process encounters an input that causes the program to execute for[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man extended period without completing, exceeding the timeout threshold set by the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzer. The error does not provide specific details about which input triggered the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimeout or at which point in the code execution the timeout occurred.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch modifies the `Type1Parser.java` file in the `fontbox` component. [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSpecifically, it targets two locations where `[0m[1;35mlexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is called within [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloops:[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **First Location [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m222[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: Within a while loop that continues until [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mspecific token conditions are met [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlooking for [0m[32m"dup"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"readonly"[0m[39m, or [0m[32m"def"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch:[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Captures the return value of `[0m[1;35mlexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` into a variable `token`[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Checks if `token` is null[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If null, throws an `IOException` with the message [0m[32m"Unexpected end of file [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mwhile reading encoding. Expected 'dup', 'readonly', or 'def'"[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Second Location [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m647[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: Within a while loop that continues until [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mit finds a literal token with text [0m[32m"CharStrings"[0m[39m. The patch:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Captures the return value of `[0m[1;35mlexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` into a variable `token`[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Checks if `token` is null[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If null, throws an `IOException` with the message [0m[32m"Unexpected end of file [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mwhile looking for CharStrings"[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch logic suggests an attempt to prevent infinite loops that might occur if [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe lexer never encounters the expected tokens and continuously returns null or if [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe end-of-file condition is not properly handled.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Result After Applying Patch[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the libFuzzer timeout error persists unchanged. This [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicates that:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The timeout is not caused by the specific scenarios the patch addresses [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnull [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtoken returns[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The infinite loop or performance bottleneck causing the timeout likely exists [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39melsewhere in the code[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The lexer may not be returning null in the problematic cases, so the added null [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks are not being triggered[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas Requiring Further Investigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo gain a holistic view of the timeout issue, the following areas should be [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvestigated:[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Lexer Implementation**: The `Type1Lexer` class should be examined to [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munderstand:[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How `[0m[1;35mpeekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mnextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` behave with malformed or malicious input[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether these methods can enter infinite loops themselves[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How end-of-file conditions are detected and reported[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Loop Termination Conditions**: Both while loops identified in the patch should[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe analyzed for:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether the peek conditions can ever become true with certain inputs[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If there are inputs that could cause the lexer to continuously advance without[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmeeting termination conditions[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether the peek operations themselves could be expensive or cause timeouts[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Input Characteristics**: Understanding what type of fuzzer input triggers the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimeout:[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The structure and size of the problematic input[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether it contains specific patterns that exploit parser weaknesses[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Other Loops in Type1Parser**: The entire `Type1Parser.java` file should be [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreviewed for:[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Other similar while loops that may lack proper termination guarantees[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Recursive parsing calls that might lead to deep call stacks[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any operations within loops that might have quadratic or worse complexity[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Token Stream Behavior**: Investigation into whether:[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The token stream can become circular or repetitive[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The peek operation might be causing repeated expensive parsing[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - There are state management issues in the lexer that prevent proper advancement[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Performance Profiling**: If possible, profiling information should be gathered[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto identify:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Which specific method or loop consumes the most time during timeout[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The call stack at the time of timeout[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Memory allocation patterns that might indicate issues[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m29[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m30[0m[39m: * @see Type1Parser[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m31[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m32[0m[39m: * The PostScript language, of which Type [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m fonts are a subset, has a[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m33[0m[39m: * somewhat awkward lexical structure. It is neither regular nor[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m34[0m[39m: * context-free, and the execution of the program can modify the[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m35[0m[39m: * the behaviour of the lexer/parser.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m36[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m37[0m[39m: * Nevertheless, this class represents an attempt to artificially separate[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m38[0m[39m: * the PostScript parsing process into separate lexing and parsing phases[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m39[0m[39m: * in order to reduce the complexity of the parsing phase.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m40[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m41[0m[39m: * @see [0m[32m"PostScript Language Reference 3rd ed, Adobe Systems [0m[32m([0m[32m1999[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m42[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m43[0m[39m: * @author John Hewson[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
